From the graph of $xy = 1,$ we can tell that the foci will be at the points $(t,t)$ and $(-t,-t)$ for some positive real number $t.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

real func(real x) {
  return(1/x);
}

pair P;
pair[] F;

P = (1/2,2);
F[1] = (sqrt(2),sqrt(2));
F[2] = (-sqrt(2),-sqrt(2));

draw(graph(func,1/3,3),red);
draw(graph(func,-3,-1/3),red);
draw((-3,0)--(3,0));
draw((0,-3)--(0,3));
draw(F[1]--P--F[2]);

